Following are the detailed findings from the Sierra Leone micro-data.

A. Abortion Incidence and Intentions among Women in the Sierra Leone

District Survey

In many cases, the men involved did not wish to discuss the incident or did not

know that the women had been pregnant (one in three). As a result, those co-

residing partners were not included in the analysis below.8

Among women who were married, about 2 in 5 (two estimated figures of 42

and 41.6) reported an unintended birth out of the prior seven intentions.9

A total of 3.6 per cent of women with estimating figures of 3.1 and 3.6 had an

unintended live birth in the prior seven births.

Because adolescent women seldom go against the family wishes and marry

early, married adolescents are not included here. Half of the unintended

live births (50.2 and 50.1 per cent) occurred in this group and half in the
